  "rag_context_preview": "---\nSOURCE: onboarding_guide.md\nThis is the primary source of onboarding documentation.\n\n---\n\n# What is Onboarding?\n\nOnboarding is the structured process of enabling a new employee to become productive, secure, and aligned with company standards.\n\nIt includes:\n\n- Role context and architecture overview\n- Required system access and permissions\n- Training plan\n- Compliance and security awareness\n- Manager alignment\n- Team integration\n\n---\n\n# Onboarding Process Overview\n\n## Phase 1: Pre-Day 0\n\n- HR profile creation\n- Account provisioning (IAM, Email, Teams)\n- Hardware setup\n- Documentation access preparation\n- Training scheduling\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Day 0 (First Login)\n\n---\nSOURCE: onboarding_guide.md\n---\n\n# Required System Access (Role Based)\n\n## For SRE / DevOps Roles\n\n- IAM account\n- Jira project access\n- GitHub repository access\n- Confluence space access\n- Monitoring dashboards\n- CI/CD pipeline access\n- DevOps Deploy App\n- Microsoft Teams\n- Outlook mailbox\n\n---\n\n# Training Plan\n\n## Week 1\n\n- Company culture & values\n- Architecture overview\n- Infrastructure walkthrough\n- Security compliance overview\n\n## Week 2\n\n- Kubernetes best practices\n- Incident response training\n- Deployment pipe\n...\n",
